text:
It's  a convenient MRT station that extends the accessible  bus route to Joo Chiat and Katong.
It's clean.
It's close to the Eunos Wet Market, coffee shops, and many senior Activities Centres.
It's  also close  to Ubi Industrial Estates.
It's  close to the Connector that is good for
stroll as well as cycling.
This MRT made transport easier, Its just far away from me and takes like 10 minutes to get here depending on how fast I walk.
Spacious hawker centre with quite a number of "popular" foods esp for the Muslim community... Just right next to the Eunos MRT station...

The state of the toilet. Horrifying. Been like that for years and years. Broken , dirty and smelly. And the smell can be felt from the entrance. But staff all nice and clean and smart looking. That part, always maintained. Must look good. Salute!

The station does not have a ramp for the disabled who are on wheel chairs and people who are carrying baggage to and from.airport to the car park onnthe SIMS avenue exit.There are lot of commuters from this side ofnthe train station.Pls have a Ramp towards the Sims avenue side
